 1959]]\n", "name_user": "C2A", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(correcting number of seats)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/London_Underground_1959_Stock"}
{"title_page": "Vasilis Genitsaridis", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=April 2013}}\n\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Vasilis Genitsaridis\n| image =\n| height = {{height|m=1.82}}\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1982|2|16|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Greece]]\n| position = Defender and Midfielder\n| currentclub = \n| clubnumber = \n| years1 = 2001\u20132003\n| years2 = 2003\u20132005\n| years3 = 2005\u20132007\n| years4 = 2007\u20132008\n| years5 = 2008\u20132009\n| years6 = 2009\u20132010\n| years7 = 2010\u20132011\n| years8 = 2011\n| clubs1 = [[Agios Nikolaos F.C.|Agios Nikolaos]]\n| clubs2 = [[Apollon Kalamarias F.C.|Apollon Kalamarias]]\n| clubs3 = [[Kalamata F.C.|Kalamata]]\n| clubs4 = [[Olympiakos Volou 1937 F.C.|Olympiakos Volou]]\n| clubs5 = Kalamata\n| clubs6 = [[Atsalenios F.C.|Atsalenios]]\n| clubs7 = [[Panachaiki]]\n| clubs8 = [[Olympiakos Chersonissos F.C.|Olympiakos Chersonissos]]\n| caps1 = \n| caps2 = 19\n| caps3 = 49\n| caps4 = 7\n| caps5 = 44\n| caps6 = 25\n| caps7 = 7\n| caps8 = 12\n| goals1 = \n| goals2 = 0\n| goals3 = 0\n| goals4 = 0\n| goals5 = 0\n| goals6 = 4\n| goals7 = 0\n| goals8 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = \n| nationalteam1 = \n| nationalcaps1 = \n| nationalgoals1 = \n| pcupdate = 1 July 2011\n| ntupdate =\n}}\n'''Vasilis Genitsaridis''' ({{lang-el|\u0392\u03b1\u03c3\u03af\u03bb\u03b7\u03c2 \u0393\u03b5\u03bd\u03b9\u03c4\u03c3\u03b1\u03c1\u03af\u03b4\u03b7\u03c2}}; born 16 February 1982) is a former professional [[Association football|footballer]] who played as a centre back and defensive midfielder for several clubs in Greece, including a stint with [[Apollon Kalamarias F.C.]] in the [[Alpha Ethniki]].\n\n==Career==\nBorn in Greece, Genitsaridis began playing football with local side [[Agios Nikolaos F.C.]] in the [[Beta Ethniki]]. In 2003, he signed with Apollon Kalamarias and helped the club gain promotion to the top flight, where he would make eight appearances during the following season.\n\nIn June 2010, Genitsaridis signed a two-year contract with [[Football League 2 (Greece)|Football League 2]] side [[Panachaiki]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Thebest.gr|script-title=el:\u03a3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u03a0\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03c7\u03b1\u03ca\u03ba\u03ae \u03bf \u0392\u03b1\u03c3\u03af\u03bb\u03b7\u03c2 \u0393\u03b5\u03bd\u03b9\u03c4\u03c3\u03b1\u03c1\u03af\u03b4\u03b7\u03c2|trans-title=Vasilis Genitsaridis in Panachaiki|url=http://www.thebest.gr/news/index/viewStory/19816|language=Greek|date=18 June 2010}}</ref> He left the club six months later, and would finish his career with [[Olympiakos Chersonissos F.C.]] in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Sportfm.gr|script-title=el:\u0388\u03ba\u03bb\u03b5\u03b9\u03c3\u03b5 \u0393\u03b5\u03bd\u03b9\u03c4\u03c3\u03b1\u03c1\u03af\u03b4\u03b7 \u03b7 \u03a7\u03b5\u03c1\u03c3\u03cc\u03bd\u03b7\u03c3\u03bf\u03c2|trans-title=Chersonissos closes deal with Genitsaridis|url=http://www.sporfm.gr/permalink/5206.html|language=Greek|date=7 January 2011}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.epae.org/player.fds?categ=2&team=43&player=7571&pagecode=04.02.02&langid=1 Profile] at EPAE.org\n*[http://guardian.touch-line.com/?CTID=57&CPID=120&TEID=1403&PLID=188837&pStr=Player Guardian Football]\n*[http://www.onsports.gr/onstats/soccer/player/1524-Genitsaridis-Basilis Profile] at Onsports.gr\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Genitsaridis, Vasilis}}\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Greek footballers]]\n[[Category:Agios Nikolaos F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Apollon Pontou FC players]]\n[[Category:Kalamata F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Olympiacos Volou 1937 F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Panachaiki F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=April 2013}}\n\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Vasilis Genitsaridis\n| image =\n| height = {{height|m=1.82}}\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1982|2|16|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Greece]]\n| position = Defender and Midfielder\n| currentclub = \n| clubnumber = \n| years1 = 2001\u20132003\n| years2 = 2003\u20132005\n| years3 = 2005\u20132007\n| years4 = 2007\u20132008\n| years5 = 2008\u20132009\n| years6 = 2009\u20132010\n| years7 = 2010\u20132011\n| years8 = 2011\n| clubs1 = Agios Nikolaos \n| clubs2 = [[Apollon Kalamarias F.C.|Apollon Kalamarias]]\n| clubs3 = [[Kalamata F.C.|Kalamata]]\n| clubs4 = [[Olympiakos Volou 1937 F.C.|Olympiakos Volou]]\n| clubs5 = Kalamata\n| clubs6 = [[Atsalenios F.C.|Atsalenios]]\n| clubs7 = [[Panachaiki]]\n| clubs8 = [[Olympiakos Chersonissos F.C.|Olympiakos Chersonissos]]\n| caps1 = \n| caps2 = 19\n| caps3 = 49\n| caps4 = 7\n| caps5 = 44\n| caps6 = 25\n| caps7 = 7\n| caps8 = 12\n| goals1 = \n| goals2 = 0\n| goals3 = 0\n| goals4 = 0\n| goals5 = 0\n| goals6 = 4\n| goals7 = 0\n| goals8 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = \n| nationalteam1 = \n| nationalcaps1 = \n| nationalgoals1 = \n| pcupdate = 1 July 2011\n| ntupdate =\n}}\n'''Vasilis Genitsaridis''' ({{lang-el|\u0392\u03b1\u03c3\u03af\u03bb\u03b7\u03c2 \u0393\u03b5\u03bd\u03b9\u03c4\u03c3\u03b1\u03c1\u03af\u03b4\u03b7\u03c2}}; born 16 February 1982) is a former professional [[Association football|footballer]] who played as a centre back and defensive midfielder for several clubs in Greece, including a stint with [[Apollon Kalamarias F.C.]] in the [[Alpha Ethniki]].\n\n==Career==\nBorn in Greece, Genitsaridis began playing football with local side Agios Nikolaos F.C. in the [[Beta Ethniki]]. In 2003, he signed with Apollon Kalamarias and helped the club gain promotion to the top flight, where he would make eight appearances during the following season.\n\nIn June 2010, Genitsaridis signed a two-year contract with [[Football League 2 (Greece)|Football League 2]] side [[Panachaiki]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Thebest.gr|script-title=el:\u03a3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u03a0\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03c7\u03b1\u03ca\u03ba\u03ae \u03bf \u0392\u03b1\u03c3\u03af\u03bb\u03b7\u03c2 \u0393\u03b5\u03bd\u03b9\u03c4\u03c3\